% Related paper
Circumstellar environment reconstruction in angular differential imaging: 
regularized inversion with a patch-based model of background correlations
The REXPACO algorithm.

To be submitted to Astronomy & Astrophysics.

% Authors
TO BE ADDED

% Date
July 2020.

% Content
This archive contains the following folders;

./GlobalBioIm: GlobalBioIm software optimized for image reconstructions 
through inverse-problem approaches.
Based on:
Pocket Guide to Solve Inverse Problems with GlobalBioIm,
Inverse Problems, 35-10, 2019.
E. Soubies, F. Soulez, M. T. McCann, T-A. Pham, L. Donati, T. Debarre, D. Sage, and M. Unser.
Github repository: https://github.com/Biomedical-Imaging-Group/GlobalBioIm

./add_on_GlobalBioIm: REXPACO routines
	/Cost: cost operators,
	/LinOp: linear operators of the REXPACO forward model,
	/Util
		/statistics: routines to compute the background statistics,
	/Util
		/scheme: routines to compute alternatively the background statistics and the source flux,
	/Example: main testing files to produce REXPACO reconstructions.
	/data: example of ADI data
		/dataset: example of VLT/SPHERE-IRDIS data of RY-Lup
			(wavelength, parallactic angles, PSF, ADI stack),
		/instrument: workable field-of-view and transmission of the coronagraph. 

